 ## Issues Addressed
 - `packages/api/src/routes/user.ts` (line 179): GDPR deletion did not clear `slackWebhookUrl`. Added `slackWebhookUrl: null` to the `.set(...)` call in the DELETE /me handler to anonymize this user-configured field alongside other PII.
+- `packages/worker/src/index.ts` (line 431): Replaced `process.env.JWT_SECRET!` non-null assertion with a validated `getJwtSecret()` helper that throws a clear error when the env var is missing, matching the pattern used in the API's `getAccessSecret()`.
+- `packages/worker/src/index.ts` (line 430): The duplicated HMAC signing logic had already been extracted to `@taad/crypto` by a prior session; the call now uses the validated secret accessor via `signUnsubscribeToken(alertId, getJwtSecret())`.
 
 ## Files Modified
 - packages/api/src/routes/user.ts
 - packages/api/tests/routes/user.test.ts
+- packages/worker/src/index.ts
 
 ## Files Created
 - (none)
 
 ## Notes
 - The test expectation was also updated to assert that `slackWebhookUrl: null` is included in the anonymization update call.
+- The `@taad/crypto` shared package with `signUnsubscribeToken(alertId, secret)` already existed from a prior code-writer session, so the HMAC duplication (issue 1) was already resolved at the implementation level.
+- The remaining gap was the raw `process.env.JWT_SECRET!` assertion (issue 2), which is now replaced with a validated accessor that throws `"JWT_SECRET environment variable is required"` when the var is absent.
